1. Dir is just a ( folder )
2. command <argument> <options>
3. echo $HOME
4. echo ~
5. cd ( change directory )
6. mkdir ( make directory )
7. ls <dir> list files and directories
8. there are two types of commands in linxu
9. shell builtin like (echo, type, ls, cd, ...)
10. external command or file usually in /usr/bin or /bin
11. touch <filename>   to create a new file
12. mkdir -p           to create directory with it's parents 
13. rm <filename>      remove a file
14. rm -r <dirname>    to remove a directory with all it's content
15. rmdir <dirname>    to remove an empty directory
16. mv source destination to rename a file or move a file from a dir to another dir
17. type <command name> to see if a command is shell builtin or a file



1. cd ..  to change directory to the parent directory for current directory (. is current dir, .. is parent dir)
2. tar -cvf <arch filename> <files of file> 
-c for create
-v for verbose
-f for file
3. gzip <filename> will compress the file with .gz extension
4. tar with -z option will arch and compress the files using gzip
5. cat to display content of a file
6. zcat to display conent of compressed file
7. grep <pattern> <filename> to find a pattern in a file
8. grep -r <pattern> <dir> to find a pattern in all files in a dir
9. find <dir> -name <filename> 
dir to search in 
filename file you are searching for
